AB  - This paper develops and examines a model of a small country operating a dual exchange market system. Particular attention is paid to the rational formation of expectations of the financial market exchange rate. In the context of the present model, it is shown that rational expectations of the financial rate are formed in a manner exactly opposite to previously assumed expectations behavior.
