AB  - This paper examines Williamson's example of destabilizing speculation using an explicit difference equation specification of speculative behavior. The type of nonconvergent cyclical movements of the exchange rate that Williamson describes are found to result from expectations based on a fixed notion of the ‘normal’ rate, together with a specific level of speculation activity. A lower level of speculation results in a divergent system; a higher level in one which is dynamically stable.
